Text: Everyone is exhausted by Elisabeth's attacks.

The symptoms of possession have returned. Everyone is
immobilized except for Beta, who barely manages to
control her magic.
Aaaaaaah!!!
Claire?! Claire!

Everything is going horribly, horribly wrong.
Beta rushes over to Claire.
Claire!!!
Master Shadow, forgive me...

The next instant, surrounded by a dark mist, Claire
suddenly rises to her feet.
Are you...Claire...?!
Her eyes are now a beautiful shade of violet.

That isn't the only thing that's changed. The air
about her feels more mature, and the quality of
her magic seems different too.
Mm... My first taste of freedom in about a month?
The Calamity Witch...!
What're you doing here? Where's Claire?!
Claire...? Ohh...you mean this look?
Same as him and all of you.
It's easier to move when I'm my own height.

Oh, and the color isn't because of magic. It's the
reflection of the light—
This will be a tough one to pull off.
Alright.
Well then.
Let's see how much this girl's body can withstand.

Elisabeth once again launches the blood surrounding
her.

It approaches with unavoidable density and speed. All
everyone can do is stare at the hopelessness bearing
down upon them.
Everyone except her, that is.
Sorry. But I'm the original...
Aurora unleashes a black wave.

Any blood entering the wave immediately loses
momentum and comes to a halt.
*gasp*
What the...?!

Once released from your body, stealing control of
your blood is child's play.
Just like this.

Aurora takes control of the incoming blood and hurls
it back at Elisabeth.

Elisabeth doesn't dodge it—she takes the blow
head-on and is bisected.

However, she instantly transforms her bleeding wound
into a spear and retaliates against Aurora.
Feisty. Ah, the joy of being young!
All at once, the battle begins.
Each spear-like tip rushes forward to meet the enemy.

A swarm of red spears fills the air. Both combatants
are assailed from all directions. Before they can hit
their targets, they collide with their opponent's
spears, canceling each other out.

The utterly inhuman fight plays out. Nobody can tear
their gaze from the exquisitely savage battle.
Whoa, whoa, talk about no holds barred.
What chaos.
A small number of Aurora's spears reach Elisabeth.

Those spears temporarily immobilize her by severing
her limbs and torso.
That's a freebie!
I'll show you the greatest power in the world!

The next instant, a crimson magic force spreads out,
with multiple lines intersecting through the space.
What the...?!
*gasp*
H-Huh?!
Wait, don't tell me—!
The buildup of magic causes the air to waver.
...THE ALL-RANGE...
Wha—?!

The crimson magic force field surrounding the tower
vanishes.
Oh dear, seems this body can't handle it.
Excuse me...?!
It'll heal in no time. You can do it, too, can't you?
...Ngh!

As Beta watches Elisabeth, she sees her injuries
rapidly healing as she gathers magic energy around
herself.
Not again...!
It's fine. That's enough.
My work here is done.
All I needed to do was buy time until he showed up.
An ebony shadow descends on them.
Unh!
Bastard!
Looks like...the main event is here.
The time of awakening is nigh...
The time...
...of awakening...is nigh!!!
